The Corrupted Treants (The Mournful Hulks): In the deeper background, barely visible through the fog, two massive, lumbering Corrupted Treants move slowly. They are former guardians of the forest, now hollowed‑out husks filled with a pulsating, violet, fungal corruption. Their eyes are empty, glowing pits, and their branches end in sharp, obsidian talons.

The Wisps of Lost Souls (Hitodama): Throughout the swamp, dozens of tiny, floating Wisps of Lost Souls drift lazily. They are not aggressive; they are the lingering spiritual remnants of the elves who first fell. Each is a small, tear‑shaped orb of pale, cold, blue‑white light, with a single, weeping black eye in its centre.

The Ruined Elven Watchtowers: Along the western edge of the swamp, just before the land turns healthy again, two ruined, ancient, stone watchtowers stand. Their white stone is cracked and stained black, and the protective, crescent‑moon sigils carved into their lintels have been deliberately defaced and filled with a dark, hardened, violet resin.

